name: Map
description: Contains methods for the Map collection type.

clear().name: clear
clear().description: Removes all of the key-value mappings from the map.

clone().name: clone
clone().description: Makes a duplicate copy of the map.

containskey(object).name: containsKey
containskey(object).description: Returns true if the map contains a mapping for the specified key.

deepclone().name: deepClone
deepclone().description: Makes a duplicate copy of a map, including sObject records if this is a map with sObject record values.

equals(map).name: equals
equals(map).description: Compares this map with the specified map and returns true if both maps are equal; otherwise, returns false.

map2.name: map2
map2.description: The map2 argument is the map to compare this map with.

get(object).name: get
get(object).description: Returns the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if the map contains no value for this key.

getsobjecttype().name: getSObjectType
getsobjecttype().description: Returns the token of the sObject type that makes up the map values.

hashcode().name: hashCode
hashcode().description: Returns the hashcode corresponding to this map.

isempty().name: isEmpty
isempty().description: Returns true if the map has zero key-value pairs.

keyset().name: keySet
keyset().description: Returns a set that contains all of the keys in the map.

put(object,object).name: put
put(object,object).signature: public Object put(Object key, Object value)
put(object,object).overrideSignature: public override Object put(Object key, Object value)
put(object,object).description: Associates the specified value with the specified key in the map.

putall(map).name: putAll
putall(map).description: Copies all of the mappings from the specified map to the original map.

putall(sobject[]).name: putAll
putall(sobject[]).description: Adds the list of sObject records to a map declared as Map<ID, sObject> or Map<String, sObject>.

remove(key).name: remove
remove(key).description: Removes the mapping for the specified key from the map, if present, and returns the corresponding value.

size().name: size
size().description: Returns the number of key-value pairs in the map.

values().name: values
values().description: Returns a list that contains all the values in the map.

map&lt;t1,t2&gt;().name: Map<T1,T2>
map&lt;t1,t2&gt;().description: Creates a new instance of the Map class. T1 is the data type of the keys and T2 is the data type of the values.

map&lt;t1,t2&gt;(map<t1,t2>).name: Map<T1,T2>
map&lt;t1,t2&gt;(map<t1,t2>).description: Creates a new instance of the Map class and initializes it by copying the entries from the specified map. T1 is the data type of the keys and T2 is the data type of the values.

maptocopy.name: mapToCopy
maptocopy.description: The map to initialize this map with. T1 is the data type of the keys and T2 is the data type of the values. All map keys and values are copied to this map.

map&lt;id,sobject&gt;(list<sobject>).name: Map<ID,sObject>
map&lt;id,sobject&gt;(list<sobject>).description: Creates a new instance of the Map class and populates it with the passed-in list of sObject records. The keys are populated with the sObject IDs and the values are the sObjects.

recordlist.name: recordList
recordlist.description: The list of sObjects to populate the map with.
